Carlton Fields is seeking a Paralegal for the Intellectual Property Practice group of the New York office.



**Essential Duties and Responsibilities:**  

* Arrange filings, mailings and effecting service for matters in NY and NJ Federal and state courts, government agencies and other parties;
* Conduct research in Westlaw, Bloomberg and other legal databases;
* Conduct research in Relativity and other discovery management tools;
* Assist with the organization of client materials and attorney work product, including computer-based technology, in particular Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint; and
* Ability to work with other practice groups in other firm offices.


**Essential Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:**  

* Must be able to read, write and speak English;
* Strong organizational and time management skills to meet billable goal of 1600 hours without overtime;
* Advanced knowledge of all MS Office applications;
* Ability to file documents in both Federal and state courts;
* Advanced Adobe professional and Adobe Acrobat;
* Strong analytical skills;
* Strong research skills;
* Expertise in Relativity;
* Ability to multi-task and work well under pressure and meet deadlines;
* Ability to work independently as well as part of a team;


**Candidate should possess:**  

* Bachelor’s Degree (requirement)
* Minimum of five to ten years’ experience working in a law firm


